# Adding New Features - Step-by-Step Guide

## Overview

This guide walks through adding a new feature to the Weighsoft UI application, following all established patterns and conventions.

## Step 1: Create the Controller

### Option A: Individual Controller File (Recommended)

Create `app/js/controllers/my_feature.js`:

```javascript
'use strict';
angular
  .module('xenon.controllers')
  .controller('MyFeatureCtrl', function($scope, $rootScope, $state, Restangular) {
    $rootScope.Start();
    const vm = this;
    const routeName = 'my_feature';  // Match API endpoint
    
    vm.baseData = Restangular.all(routeName);
    vm.isEditing = false;
    vm.data = {};
    vm.list = [];
    
    function loadData() {
      $rootScope.Start();
      vm.baseData.getList().then(function(data) {
        vm.list = data;
        $rootScope.Loaded();
      }, function(response) {
        $rootScope.Error(response);
      });
    }
    
    vm.showAddForm = function() {
      vm.isEditing = true;
      vm.data = {};
    };
    
    vm.showEditForm = function(item) {
      $rootScope.Start();
      Restangular.one(routeName, item.id).get().then(function(data) {
        vm.data = data;
        vm.isEditing = true;
        $rootScope.Loaded();
      }, function(response) {
        vm.isEditing = false;
        $rootScope.Error(response);
      });
    };
    
    vm.saveForm = function(formData) {
      if (!formData.$valid) {
        return;
      }
      
      $rootScope.Start();
      var promise = typeof vm.data.id === 'undefined'
        ? vm.baseData.post(vm.data)
        : vm.data.save();
        
      promise.then(function() {
        vm.isEditing = false;
        loadData();
      }, function(response) {
        $rootScope.Error(response);
      });
    };
    
    vm.deleteItem = function(item) {
      if (!confirm('Are you sure you want to delete this item?')) {
        return;
      }
      $rootScope.Start();
      Restangular.one(routeName, item.id).get().then(function(data) {
        data.remove().then(function() {
          loadData();
        }, function(response) {
          $rootScope.Error(response);
        });
      });
    };
    
    vm.cancel = function() {
      vm.isEditing = false;
      $state.go('app.my_feature');
    };
    
    vm.initialize = function() {
      loadData();
    };
  });
```

### Option B: Register in controllers.js

If it's a simple controller, you can add it to `app/js/controllers.js`:

```javascript
.controller('MyFeatureCtrl', function($scope, $rootScope, $state, Restangular) {
  // ... controller code
});
```

## Step 2: Create the Template

Create `app/tpls/my_feature/list.html`:

```html
<div ng-controller="MyFeatureCtrl as System">
  <page-title 
    title="My Feature" 
    description="Manage my feature items">
  </page-title>
  
  <!-- List View -->
  <div class="panel panel-default" ng-if="!System.isEditing">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <button class="btn btn-primary" ng-click="System.showAddForm()">
        <i class="fa fa-plus"></i> Add Item
      </button>
    </div>
    <div class="panel-body">
      <table datatable="ng" class="table table-striped">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>Actions</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr ng-repeat="item in System.list">
            <td>{{ item.name }}</td>
            <td>
              <button class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" ng-click="System.showEditForm(item)">
                Edit
              </button>
              <button class="btn btn-sm btn-danger" ng-click="System.deleteItem(item)">
                Delete
              </button>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <!-- Form View -->
  <div class="panel panel-default" ng-if="System.isEditing">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <h3 class="panel-title">{{ System.data.id ? 'Edit' : 'Add' }} Item</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="panel-body">
      <form name="myForm" ng-submit="System.saveForm(myForm)" novalidate>
        <div class="form-group" ng-class="{'has-error': myForm.name.$invalid && myForm.name.$touched}">
          <label>Name</label>
          <input 
            type="text" 
            class="form-control" 
            ng-model="System.data.name"
            name="name"
            required>
          <span ng-if="myForm.name.$error.required && myForm.name.$touched" class="help-block">
            Name is required
          </span>
        </div>
        
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" ng-disabled="myForm.$invalid">
          Save
        </button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" ng-click="System.cancel()">
          Cancel
        </button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Step 3: Add the Route

Add to `app/js/routes.js`:

```javascript
state('app.my_feature', {
  url: '/my_feature',
  templateUrl: appHelper.templatePath('my_feature/list'),
  controller: 'MyFeatureCtrl as System',
  resolve: {
    deps: function ($ocLazyLoad) {
      return $ocLazyLoad.load([
        ASSETS.tables.datatables,
        ASSETS.extra.toastr,
      ]);
    },
  }
})
```

## Step 4: Add to Menu (Optional)

If the feature should appear in the sidebar menu, add to `app/js/services.js` in the `prepareSidebarMenu` function:

```javascript
if (permissions.my_feature === "true") {
  vm.Operations.addItem("My Feature", "/app/my_feature", "linecons-note");
}
```

## Step 5: Test the Feature

1. Navigate to the new route: `/app/my_feature`
2. Test adding a new item
3. Test editing an existing item
4. Test deleting an item
5. Verify loading states work correctly
6. Verify error handling works correctly

## Checklist for New Features

- [ ] Controller uses `controller as` syntax with `vm`
- [ ] Controller uses `'use strict'`
- [ ] Controller uses Restangular (not $http)
- [ ] Controller handles errors with `$rootScope.Error()`
- [ ] Controller shows/hides loading with `$rootScope.Start()` / `$rootScope.Loaded()`
- [ ] Template uses `controller as` syntax: `ng-controller="Ctrl as System"`
- [ ] Template uses `appHelper.templatePath()` (in route definition)
- [ ] Route is added to `app/js/routes.js`
- [ ] Route includes required assets in `resolve` block
- [ ] Route state name follows convention: `app.feature_name`
- [ ] File names use underscores: `my_feature.js`, `list.html`
- [ ] Controller name uses PascalCase: `MyFeatureCtrl`
- [ ] Form validation is implemented
- [ ] Navigation uses `$state.go()` (not `window.location`)

## Adding Nested/Child Features

For features with sub-features (like contracts, pallets, tares):

### Controller Structure

```
app/js/controllers/my_feature/
  my_features.controller.js    # Main controller
  list.controller.js           # List controller
  edit.controller.js          # Edit controller
```

### Route Structure

```javascript
state('app.my_feature', {
  url: '/my_feature',
  templateUrl: appHelper.templatePath('my_feature/main'),
  controller: 'MyFeaturesCtrl as System'
})

state('app.my_feature.list', {
  url: '/list/:id',
  templateUrl: appHelper.templatePath('my_feature/list'),
  controller: 'MyFeatureListCtrl as System'
})

state('app.my_feature.edit', {
  url: '/edit/:id',
  templateUrl: appHelper.templatePath('my_feature/edit'),
  controller: 'MyFeatureEditCtrl as System'
})
```

## Common Patterns Reference

### Pattern: List with Create/Edit/Delete
- See: `companies.js`, `users.js`
- Template: Single template with `ng-if` for form view

### Pattern: Master-Detail
- See: `contract/`, `pallet/`, `tare/`
- Template: Separate templates for list and detail views

### Pattern: Complex Forms
- See: `weighing_create.js`, `weighing_update.js`
- Template: Multiple form sections, state preservation

## Step 6: Update Versions and Commit

**CRITICAL: After completing any changes, you MUST:**

1. **Update version numbers** in:
   - `build.bat` - Increment `set version=0.10.X`
   - `build.sh` - Increment `version=0.10.X`
   - `app/tpls/layout/page-title.html` - Update all three version numbers
   - `package.json` - Increment `"version": "1.3.X"`

2. **Commit all changes** with a descriptive message:
   ```bash
   git add .
   git commit -m "[Feature] Description of changes

   - Change 1
   - Change 2
   - Version updated to 0.10.X"
   ```

See `09-version-control-commits.mdc` for detailed version and commit workflow.

